HEADWORD: Chromograph
<hw>Chro"mo*graph</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ color +
<ets>-graph</ets>.]</ety> <def>An apparatus by which a number of copies
of written matter, maps, plans, etc., can be made; -- called also
<altname>hectograph</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

